article.description: Jahlil Jenkins had a career-high 31 points as Fairleigh Dickinson easily defeated Wagner 106-73 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Jenkins lifts Fairleigh Dickinson over Wagner 106-73
article.linkText: Jenkins lifts Fairleigh Dickinson over Wagner 106-73
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- Jahlil Jenkins had a career-high 31 points as Fairleigh Dickinson easily defeated Wagner 106-73 on Thursday night. Jenkins made 12 of 15 shots, including 5 of 7 from deep. He added seven assists and five steals. Brandon Powell had 16 points for Fairleigh Dickinson (7-16, 5-7 Northeast Conference). Elyjah Williams added 16 points and eight rebounds. Devon Dunn had 14 points. Fairleigh Dickinson is undefeated (2-0) when scoring at least 100 points this season. The 106 points were a season best for Fairleigh Dickinson, which also posted season highs with 16 3-pointers and 26 assists. Tyrone Nesby IV scored a career-high 25 points and had eight rebounds for the Seahawks (5-18, 2-10), whose losing streak stretched to six games. Elijah Ford added 15 points and six rebounds. Curtis Cobb III had 10 points. The Knights improve to 2-0 against the Seahawks for the season. Fairleigh Dickinson defeated Wagner 68-63 on Jan. 30. Fairleigh Dickinson faces Robert Morris on the road on Saturday. Wagner matches up against Merrimack on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
